      <section eId="sec_1233">
        <num>1233</num>
        <heading>Clinging to vehicles</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_1233__subsec_i">
          <num>(i)</num>
          <content>
            <p>vehicles in an emergency operation as defined in section one\nhundred fourteen-b of this chapter; and\n  (ii) farm type tractors used exclusively for agricultural purposes or\nother farm equipment; and\n  (iii) riding on the open, uncovered cargo area of a truck with the\npermission of the operator of such truck; and\n  (iv) vehicles employed by a municipality for local garbage collection;\nand\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_1233__subsec_v">
          <num>(v)</num>
          <content>
            <p>vehicles participating in a parade pursuant to a municipal permit.\n  3. No vehicle operator shall knowingly permit any person to attach any\ndevice or himself to such operator's vehicle in violation of subdivision\none or subdivision two of this section.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
